Function Reference/wp clearcookie « WordPress Codex
-----------

This function can be replaced via
[plugins](/Glossary#plugins "Glossary"). If plugins do not redefine
these functions, then this will be used instead.

Clears the authentication cookie, logging the user out.

**This function is deprecated. Use
[`wp_clear_auth_cookie()`](/Function_Reference/wp_clear_auth_cookie "Function Reference/wp clear auth cookie")
instead.**

Usage
-----

` <?php wp_clearcookie(); ?> `

Parameters
----------

None.

Return Values
-------------

 (void) 
:   This function does not return a value.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

-   This function can be replaced via
    [plugins](/Glossary#plugins "Glossary"). If plugins do not redefine
    these functions, then this will be used instead.
-   **This function is deprecated. Use
    [`wp_set_auth_cookie()`](/Function_Reference/wp_set_auth_cookie "Function Reference/wp set auth cookie")
    instead.**

Change Log
----------

-   Since: 1.5
-   Deprecated: 2.5.0

Source File
-----------

`wp_clearcookie()` is located in `wp-includes/pluggable.php`.

